{"id": "EUVD-2021-34515", "enisaUuid": "bd5d1d60-0cb2-35ee-9fb0-cf9b29303a0a", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nALSA: pcm: oss: Fix negative period/buffer sizes\n\nThe period size calculation in OSS layer may receive a negative value\nas an error, but the code there assumes only the positive values and\nhandle them with size_t.  Due to that, a too big value may be passed\nto the lower layers.\n\nThis patch changes the code to handle with ssize_t and adds the proper\nerror checks appropriately.", "datePublished": "2024-05-24T15:09:26", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-18T11:37:48", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/be8869d388593e57223ad39297c8e54be632f2f2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/502e1146873d870f87da3b8f93d6bf2de5f38d0c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8af815ab052eaf74addbbfb556d63ce2137c0e1b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f96c0959c1ee92adc911c10d6ec209af50105049", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f12c8a7515f641885677960af450082569a87243", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/02b2b691b77cd7b951fa7b6c9d44d4e472cdc823", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/00a860678098fcd9fa8db2b5fb9d2ddf4776d4cc", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9d2479c960875ca1239bcb899f386970c13d9cfe"], "aliases": ["CVE-2021-47511"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "02c30122-2255-3908-9629-dfbe5604c0d4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.4.165"}, {"id": "183a7e91-769a-388c-8862-ee7d3b0fa365", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.4.295"}, {"id": "30db5dfe-3d8c-3eb8-aa80-0ef1f7382cfa", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <00a860678098fcd9fa8db2b5fb9d2ddf4776d4cc"}, {"id": "35c91dd2-ae98-35c7-92ca-4663d05ec3ce", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.85"}, {"id": "4c180a85-a